build_orders.title: Scouts
build_orders.description: Construcción rápida clásica: los exploradores pueden obtener el control temprano del mapa, hacer daño temprano antes de que se levanten los muros y pueden matar de manera efectiva a pequeños grupos de arqueros / hostigadores. También pueden ganar tiempo para que un jugador haga la transición a arquerias, lo que generalmente es necesario, ya que los arqueros, una vez reunidos, comenzarán a matar a los exploradores con bastante facilidad.

build_orders.title: Archers
build_orders.description: Esta es una construcción más lenta ya que los arqueros deben estar en masa para ser efectivos. El objetivo es mantener 2 arquerias funcionando constantemente; los arqueros también necesitan flecha de pluma como mínimo para ser efectivos. Esta es a menudo una configuración pobre para usar 1v1, en parte porque es bastante débil contra la configuración de scouts más rápida, por lo que se usa principalmente en juegos de equipo como flanco donde sus debilidades pueden ser cubiertas por otros jugadores.

build_orders.title: Galleys
build_orders.description: Fast all in water build order to win water by producing galleys out of 3 docks and build 5 fishing ships in dark age.

build_orders.title: Men-at-Arms → Archers
build_orders.description: Esta construcción permite crear al menos 3 milicias mientras avanza e investiga la mejora de hombres de armas al llegar a Feudal. Los hombres de armas no tienen un contraataque efectivo hasta que el oponente puede comenzar a producir arqueros, y pueden causar una interrupción importante si no están bloqueados. Esta configuración es una forma de ganar tiempo para los arqueros en masa, ya que tu oponente generalmente se ve obligado a lidiar primero con los hombres de armas en su base. Esta construcción es bastante ajustada (y, por lo tanto, difícil), lo que significa que collera generalmente debe retrasarse.

build_orders.title: Men-at-Arms → Towers
build_orders.description: Esta construcción permite crear al menos 3 milicias mientras avanza e investiga la mejora de hombres de armas al llegar a Feudal. Los hombres de armas no tienen un contraataque efectivo hasta que el oponente puede comenzar a producir arqueros, y pueden causar una interrupción importante si no están bloqueados. Esta construcción es bastante ajustada (y, por lo tanto, difícil), lo que significa que collera generalmente debe retrasarse. Las torres se pueden usar para negar el control del mapa y los recursos, y dado que los hombres de armas no tienen contraataques en el feudal temprano, son ideales para proteger a los aldeanos avanzados.

build_orders.title: Drush - Archers
build_orders.description: Una fiebre de la Edad Oscura: tres milicias creadas en la Edad Oscura solían retrasar al oponente. Esta es otra forma de ganar tiempo para los arqueros en masa. En el momento de escribir este artículo, esta configuración se ha vuelto menos popular, y se prefiere la configuración de hombres de armas. Puede ser una semana bastante para la construcción de hombres de armas, ya que el oponente tendrá milicias para defender, que luego se pueden actualizar después de que golpeen a Feudal primero. También se puede usar un drush para ganar tiempo para realizar un Caslte rápido. Esto también ha pasado de moda en el momento de escribir este artículo, aunque a veces todavía se puede lograr con un buen mapa. Investiga el emplumado como mínimo para las ballestas.

build_orders.title: Drush - FC & Crossbows
build_orders.description: A Dark Age rush: three militia created in Dark Age used to delay the opponent. This is another way of buying time to mass archers. At time of writing, this build has become less popular, with the men-at-arms build being preferred. It can be quite week agains the men-at-arms build, since the opponent will have militia to defend, which can then be upgraded after they hit Feudal first. A drush can also be used to buy time to perform a fast Caslte. This has als gone out of fashion at the time of writing, though it can still sometimes be pulled off with a good map. Research fletching as a minimum for the crossbows.

build_orders.title: Drush FC into Crossbows
build_orders.description: The Drush Fast Castle is viable on any open map that has the potential for walling such as Arabia. Yet it does depend on the kind of map that is generated. You want close natural barriers so that you don't have to wall too much and you want safe resources so you can't be attacked easily from outside the walls by towers and feudal archers. This build works with any civ, but especially well with Vietnamese, Aztecs, Britons, Goths, Celts, Vikings, Mayans, and Ethiopians.

build_orders.title: Fast Imperial
build_orders.description: Generic build. Pushing deer would improve these builds. Get double-bit axe while advancing to Castle. Turks are one of the most viable for a fast imperial due to their strong, faster gunpowder. For Turks, send just 1 to Gold from Wood after clicking Feudal and build Barracks while advancing to Feudal age and then a Range instead of a Market.

build_orders.title: Fast Castle Knights
build_orders.description: Usually done from pocket position in team games. Knights are ideal from this position because of their mobility, but the crossbowmen build might occasionally be used depending on the civ. This allows for at least six knights to be produced from both, following by constant production from one stable. For Crossbows, build ranges instead and go 8 on gold.

build_orders.title: Fast Castle Unique Units
build_orders.description: Fast castle and have the stone to build one when reach it. Sometimes used as pocket with civs such as Burmese/Mayans/Spanish. Eco balance while advancing to Castle will vary according to the civ and their unique unit.

build_orders.title: Fast Castle Boom
build_orders.description: Place two extra town centers upon hitting Castle and maintain production from all three. In Castle, set all gather points to wood, and build farms as soon as wood becomes available. Leaving villagers on gold means food can be bought if needed, and it can also be used to buy stone for a fourth town center later. Usually, only used on closed maps.

build_orders.title: Fast Castle
build_orders.description: One of the most common strategies in multiplayer games is the Fast Castle Age strategy. The goal is to get to the Castle Age as fast as possible.

build_orders.title: Mayan Men-at-Arms → Archers
build_orders.description: A man-at-arms build that focuses on transitioning into one range archers and focusing on economy to reach the next age quicker before going for a second range. A sub 20 min castle age after rushing with men-at-arms and fast fletching archers is insane and will allow you to flat out end games immediately.

build_orders.title: Hybrid: 1 Dock + 2 Ranges
build_orders.description: A build for hybrid maps like Costal, Continental, Highland, Rivers, Scandinavia, etc. that is more focused on land than on water. In this build order, we start off with a dock in Dark age to make use of the fish, and then we quickly transition into a more land approch in Feudal age. Best civs for this are Japanes, Malians, Mayans, or Mongols. Other top civs for this build order and hybrid maps are Huns, Byzantines, or Koreans.

build_orders.title: Galleys
build_orders.description: Generic water build; fast Feudal with four fishing ships, followed by constant production from two, then three docks shortly after. Usually start with fire galleys; fletching is necessary if switching to galleys.

build_orders.title: Fast Castle
build_orders.description: Generic build. Pushing deer for an eco-boost and earlier up-time is standard on Arena, but these builds can be done without. Also, skip loom if possible for these builds. Fors fast Castle with stable/range advance with +1 pop.

build_orders.title: Fast Castle Drop
build_orders.description: A little faster than the other Fast Castle build, but with a weaker economy.

build_orders.title: Fast Castle Selling Wood
build_orders.description: Collect 30 gold without a mining camp and sell 100 wood in Feudal for a faster Castle time. Skip loom.

build_orders.title: Fast Imperial, Castle Drop
build_orders.description: Castle drop into fast Imperial for trebs.

build_orders.title: Eagles
build_orders.description: Straight eagle scouts; allows constant production from two barracks upon reaching Feudal. Requires both blacksmith upgrades early on for them to be effective. Could be followed either by ranges for archer transition, or a third brracks for full eagles. Usually not viable against experienced opponents, with men-at-arms - eagles being a better (but still uncommon) option. Aztecs are the most viable for this build due to the shorter creation time. (More commonly, eagle scouts would begin massing in late Feudal so there is an army ready to upgrade upon reaching Castle.)

build_orders.title: Mongol Scouts
build_orders.description: The Mongol scout rush is their signature strategy and an important one to learn, since after their fast start they get few other advantages until mid-late imp.

build_orders.title: Korean Towers
build_orders.description: Towers are the only thing the Koreans are good at, so it's worth knowing a build for them. Can be used with other civs but will be less effective.

build_orders.title: Persian Douche
build_orders.description: An early game rush that includes deleting and rebuilding your town center next to your opponent's town center. This strategy can only be executed with Persians since there town center has twice the HP.

build_orders.title: Inka Villager & Tower Rush
build_orders.description: A player made famous by a legend video released by T90, Noboru developed this build and was defeating players with much higher elo than himself.

build_orders.title: Aztec Smush
build_orders.description: The Aztecs have always been a deadly Arena civ, mostly for the fact that they can grab map control decisively with their stronger monks and eagle warriors. This strategy tries to highlight this strength by using that same map control and going aggressive with Monks and Siege.

build_orders.title: Britons Fast Archers
build_orders.description: Compared to a standard 23pop double range build, this build produces the first group of archers faster. It's more flexible as well since it's not as easily countered by one range skirms, because we don't blindly invest in a 2nd range in early feudal.

build_orders.title: Lithuanian 3 Minute Rush
build_orders.description: Taking advantage of the 150 food bonus of the Lithuanians to have 2 milita out after 3 minutes for the fastest possible rush. After you built the lumber camp, you can lure your first boar and continue a standard build like archers scouts, or fast castle.

build_orders.title: Vietnamese Quick Archers
build_orders.description: Taking advantage of three bonuses the Vietnamese get to make this quick rush possible. 1. Economic upgrades cost no wood, meaning not as many lumberjacks are needed when hitting Feudal. 2. The enemy position is revealed from the start, which allows pushing two deer with the scout before you send your scout to the enemy's base. 3. Archers have +20% HP, which makes them tankier. Note that the 2nd lumber camp needs to wait until 2 ranges and the blacksmith are up. With this build you get a constant archer production as with the default archer build - except 1:15 minutes earlier - and a similar Castle time.

build_orders.title: Double Castle Arambai
build_orders.description: Fastest way to get to two castles constantly producing Arambai.

build_orders.title: Standard 21 Pop Fast Feudal
build_orders.description: This is a non specialiced fast Feudal build. Most standard Feudal rushing builds only have slight adjustments to this one.

build_orders.title: Khmer Scouts
build_orders.description: The Khmer scouts build can be almost as good as the Mongol build.

build_orders.title: Khmer Fast Castle
build_orders.description: Standard Fast Castle build adapted for the Khmer.

build_orders.title: Byzantine Fast Imperial
build_orders.description: Arena build. Byzantines are one of the best civs for a fast Imperial due to the reduced cost, and they have strong options including monks and gunpowder.

build_orders.title: Malay Scouts
build_orders.description: The standard scout build adapted for the Malay bonus.

build_orders.title: Malay Archers
build_orders.description: The standard archer build adapted for the Malay bonus.

build_orders.title: Malay Fast Castle
build_orders.description: Generic Fast Castle build adapted for the Malay bonus.

build_orders.title: Malay Fast Castle + Eco
build_orders.description: Generic Fast Castle build adapted for the Malay bonus.

build_orders.title: Cuman Feudal TC Boom
build_orders.description: A quick build to get as fast as possible to the Cuman double Town Center boom. This is a very flexible build order and can be adapted in Feudal Age depending on the situation.

build_orders.title: Khmer Scout Rush
build_orders.description: In the quest for the fast scrushes, it seems that Khmer have risen to the occasion with a scrush uptime that rivals the Mongols. While this build is extremely lean, it can be adapted to go up at 17/18 population as well in order to adjust for the game being played.

build_orders.title: Frank Scout Rush
build_orders.description: A faster scout rush build with the Franks making sure to hit your opponent before walls go up which makes use on the berry bonus.

build_orders.title: Hoang Rush
build_orders.description: Hoang is infamous for climbing the laddet with one strategy, and one strategy only: A Celtic rush in Dark Age, and then goging for a fast Castle Age to start applying pressure with siege, knights, and monks.

build_orders.title: Saracens Fast Castle
build_orders.description: One of the most common strategies in multiplayer games is the Fast Castle Age strategy. The goal is to get to the Castle Age as fast as possible.

build_orders.title: Men-at-Arms Flud
build_orders.description: Get as fast as possible to Men-at-Arms and make use of the Japanese bonus of faster attacking infantry to overwhelm your opponent before they can even think about clicking up.

build_orders.title: Lithuanian Hybrid Fast Castle
build_orders.description: This is the best opening for Lithuanians on Four Lakes. It can probably be used for other maps where you have fairly safe fish as well. If you’re going crossbowmen, get 9 on gold (for 2 ranges). You can afford a university + ballistics and even some siege since you have so many lumberjacks.

build_orders.title: Lithuanian Scout Rush
build_orders.description: Lithuanians are basically the new mongols, in terms of how fast they can get up to feudal and get their scout rush going. This is the best scout rush build order and timing to be able to sustain production in feudal, as well as get up very quickly.

build_orders.title: Lithuanian Skirm + Spear Rush
build_orders.description: Lithuanians start with +150 food which allows going up faster. They also have a bonus that makes their spearman-line and skirmishers move 10% faster. These two bonuses make the Skirm + Spear rush strategy so viable.

build_orders.title: Malay Elephants
build_orders.description: A battle elephant rush build that makes use of two Malay bonuses: cheaper elphants and 66% faster age uptime. This build makes sure you can pump out elephants and keep villager production from one TC going at the same time.

build_orders.title: Bulgarian Trush
build_orders.description: A build that makes use of the free milita-line upgrades the Bulgarians get to make a tower rush more cost effective and faster.

build_orders.title: Malay Stampede
build_orders.description: An all-in battle elephant rush build that makes use of two Malay bonuses: cheaper elphants and 66% faster age uptime. After reaching the Castle Age, the TC will be idled to maintain two stable elephant production.

build_orders.title: Japanese Men-at-Arms
build_orders.description: A build that allows for creating 3 milita while advancing and researching the men-at-arms upgrade upon hitting Feudal but adapted for the Japanese wood bonus that allows going up with 20 pop instead of the standard 22 pop. You then can follow up with archers or towers.

11.description: Also move 2 villagers from sheep to build farms.

12.title: 1 Sheep → 1 Farm

14.title: Loom + 22 Pop Feudal
14.description: Now research loom, and then click Feudal with 22 population.

15.title: Loom + 23 Pop Feudal
15.description: Now research loom, and then click Feudal with 23 population.

16.title: 3 Sheep → 3 Wood
16.description: Now move 3 villagers from sheep to wood.

17.title: 2 Sheep → 2 Wood (Straggler Trees)
17.description: Now move 2 villagers to straggler trees.

18.title: Barracks
18.description: Now build a barracks before you reach the Feudal age.

19.title: Stable, Double-Bit Axe + Horse Collar
19.description: Now build a stable with at least 2 villagers, and research both double-bit axe and horse collar. (Set the TC gather point to nearby straggler trees.)

20.title: ↑14 Farms

22.title: Choice
22.description: Transition into archers, skirmishers, or go for a fast castle.

23.title: 5 on Gold
23.description: Send the next 5 villagers to gold.

24.title: Blacksmith
24.description: You will then need to build a blacksmith.

27.title: 2 Ranges
27.description: Next build 2 ranges as soon as you have the wood, and start producing archers from both ranges.

30.title: 2 on Gold (Collect 40 Gold)
30.description: Collect 40 Gold with the next 2 villagers.

31.title: 4 on Gold
31.description: Send the next 4 villagers to gold.

32.title: 2 Ranges + Double-Bit Axe
32.description: Now immediately place 2 ranges, and research double-bit axe.

33.title: ↑12 Farms

35.title: Horse Collar + Move to Farms
35.description: Research horse collar before moving the villagers on sheep to build new farms.

36.title: ↑18 Farms
36.description: Once you have enough villagers on gold, the next villagers should all go to farms. (Set the TC gather point to nearby straggler trees.)

38.title: 1 Builds Barracks
38.description: Now build a barracks with the next villager.

39.title: 2 on Gold
39.description: The next 2 villagers should go to gold.

41.title: 4 Sheep → 4 Farms
41.description: Move 4 villagers from sheep to farms.

42.title: Men-at-Arms + Double-bit Axe
42.description: Also start moving villagers from sheep to make farms.

43.title: Collect 10 Gold After Barracks Is Built
43.description: Now send the builder to collect 10 gold.

44.title: 3 Sheep → 3 Farms
44.description: Move 3 villagers to make farms around the TC once you have the wood.

45.title: 1 Gold → 1 Wood
45.description: The gold villager should now go to take wood.

46.title: Loom + 28 Pop Feudal
46.description: Now research loom, and then click Feudal with 28 population.

47.title: 9 Sheep → 5 Wood + 4 Gold
47.description: Now move more villagers to wood, so that you have 12 split between 2 lumber camps. And move 4 to mine gold.

48.title: 1 Starts Walling
48.description: Send the next villager to wall your base.

50.title: 6 on Gold
50.description: Send the next 6 villagers to gold.

51.title: ↑18 Farms
51.description: Once you have enough villagers on gold, the next villagers should all go to farms. (Set the TC gather point to nearby straggler trees.)

52.title: 2 on Berries
52.description: Now send the next 2 villagers to berries.

53.title: Move to Farms
53.description: Start moving villagers from under the town center to make new farms, every time you have 60 wood in the bank.

54.title: Loom + 32 Pop Feudal
54.description: Now research loom, and then click Feudal with 32 population.

57.title: 3 on Gold
57.description: Now send the next 3 villagers to gold.

58.title: Loom + 27 Pop Feudal
58.description: Now research loom, and then click Feudal with 27 population.

59.title: Sheep → ↑8 Farms
59.description: As the sheep run out, continue moving villagers to farms until you have 8 farms.

60.title: 2 on Wood
60.description: Send the next 2 villagers to wood.

62.title: Double-Bit Axe + Horse Collar
62.description: Research both double- bit axe and horse collar.

63.title: 2 Town Centers
63.description: Immediately place 2 town centres, tasking about 4 villagers to build each one. Set the town center gather pain to wood and move villagers to build farms every time you have 60 wood.

65.title: Buy Stone for 4th Town Center
65.description: You can now buy 100 stone, and start saving wood for a 4th town center.

66.title: 6 on Wood
66.description: Now send more villagers to wood, until you have 10 villagers split between two lumber camps.

67.title: 8 Sheep → 8 Farms
67.description: Move villagers to farms until you have 8 farms.

68.title: Stable + Blacksmith
68.description: After reaching Feudal, immediately build a stable and a blacksmith.

70.title: 2nd Stable
70.description: Also remember to build a 2nd stable before you reach the Castle age.

72.title: 2 Sheep → 2 Stone
72.description: Now move another 2 villagers to stone.

73.title: 7 Sheep → 7 Farms
73.description: As the sheep run out, continue moving villagers to farms until you have 7 farms.

74.title: Build Castle
74.description: Build a castle using all of the villagers from stone.

75.description: Now build a range and a blacksmith.

76.description: Now send the next 4 villagers to wood. Send only 3 if you want to advance quicker.

83.description: Send 5 villagers from sheep to mine stone.

84.title: 3 Sheep + 2 Gold → Forward
84.description: Send 5 villagers forward to build towers after you have 40 gold for the Men-at-Arms upgrade.

85.title: 7 on Sheep
85.description: Now send the next 7 villagers to sheep/boar.

86.title: 7 Sheep → 7 Wood
86.description: Now move 7 villagers from sheeps to wood.

87.title: Loom + 25 Pop Feudal
87.description: Now research loom, and then click Feudal with 25 population.

88.description: Now send the next 6 villagers to sheep.

90.title: 4 Berries → 4 Wood
90.description: Now move 4 villagers from berries to wood.

94.description: Build 6 farms with villagers from sheep.

95.description: Now build a market and a blacksmith.

96.description: Now research Scale Mail Armor at the blacksmith.

97.description: Send the next villager to lure the 2nd boar.

98.title: 3 on Berries
98.description: Have the next 3 villagers also forage for berries.

99.title: Builder → Wood
99.description: Send the builder to chop wood once they are done with building.

100.title: 3 on Sheep
100.description: Send the next 3 villagers to sheep/boar.

101.title: House + Walling
101.description: Have 1 villager from under the town center build a house and start walling.

104.title: Straggler Trees + Move to Farms
104.description: Once sheeps are depleted, move the villagers under the town center to nearby straggler trees and build farms as soon as you can.

106.title: 10 Archers
106.description: Keep producing archers unitl you have 10. Make sure to build enough houses.

107.title: Bowsaw + Horse Collar
107.description: Research both bowsaw and horse collar.

108.title: Bodkin Arrow + Padded Armor
108.description: Research bodkin arrow as well as padded armor to maker raiding with your archers as effective as possible.

109.title: Crossbowman
109.description: Research Crossbowman at the archery range.

110.title: 2 Farms → 2 Wood
110.description: Send the first 2 farmers whose farms expire to chop wood.

111.title: 2nd Town Center
111.description: Build a 2nd town center with 3 villagers and start producing villagers out of both town centers.

112.description: The next villager builds a house next to coast where they will then build a dock. Afterwards, they will build a 2nd house. If the villager is done, let them collect shore fish near the dock.

113.title: 4 Fishing Ships
113.description: Make a new fishing ship as soon as you get 75 wood unitl you have 4 fishing ships.

114.title: ↑15 on Sheep (incl. Builder)
114.description: Send the next villagers to sheep/boar and the dock builder as well until you have 15 below the town center.

115.title: Loom + 26 Pop Feudal
115.description: Now research loom, and then click Feudal with 26 population. (With 21 villagers, 1 scout, and 4 ships.)

116.title: 11 Sheep → 11 Wood

117.title: 4 Sheep → 4 Gold
117.description: The remaining villagers from sheep should mine gold.

118.title: 2 Fire Galleys
118.description: Build two fire galleys upon reaching Feudal age. Add more when you have the resources and your opponent adds more as well.

119.title: Mill + 4 on Berries
119.description: The next 4 villagers should go to berries.

120.title: 6 Wood → 6 Farms

121.title: ↑13 Farms
121.description: The next 7 villagers should all go to farms. (Set the TC gather point to nearby straggler trees.)

122.title: Horse Collar + Gold Mining Upgrade
122.description: On your way to Castle age, get horse collar and the gold mining upgrade.

123.title: Padded Archer Armor
123.description: On your way to Castle age, also get the padded archer armor upgrade.

124.title: 6 on Sheep
124.description: Send the next 6 villagers to sheep/boar.

125.title: Loom + 25 Pop Feudal
125.description: Now research loom, and then click Feudal with 25 population. (With 20 villagers, 1 scout, and 4 ships.)

128.description: Also build a 2nd dock before you reach the Feudal age.

131.description: The next 8 villagers should go to berries.

132.title: 8 on Farms

133.title: 8 Berries → 8 Wood

137.description: Now send the next 4 villagers to build farms.

139.description: Now send the next 4 or 5 villagers to wood.

140.title: Barracks Before Feudal (When Military Plan)
140.description: Now build a barracks before you reach the Feudal age.

141.title: Or Stable/Range (When Military Plan)
141.description: Or go for a stable/range instead of a market.

143.title: Collect 30 Gold
143.description: Collect 30 gold with the next villager without building a mining camp.

146.title: 4 on Sheep
146.description: Now send the next 4 villagers to sheep/boar.

147.title: 12 Sheep → 12 Farms
147.description: When sheep run out start building farms until you have 12.

149.description: Send 2 lumber jacks to mine gold.

150.title: Monestry + Siege Workshop
150.description: Now build a monestry and a siege workshop.

153.title: 4 Wood → 4 Stone
153.description: Send 2 lumber jacks to mine gold.

155.title: 2 Barracks Before Feudal
155.description: Now build 2 barracks before you reach the Feudal age.

156.title: 2 (3) on Sheep
156.description: Now send the next 2 (or 3) villagers to sheep/boar.

158.title: 5 Sheep → 5 Wood
158.description: Now move 5 more villagers to wood.

159.title: Stable
159.description: Now build a stable with at least 2 villagers.

160.title: Lure Boar + 2 More on Boar
160.description: Now send the next villager to lure the boar, then add 2 more villager to sheep.

161.title: 5 on Sheep
161.description: Now send the next 5 villagers to sheep/boar.

162.title: Loom + 19 Pop Feudal
162.description: Now research loom, and then click Feudal with 19 population.

163.title: 2 Sheep → 2 Wood
163.description: Now move another 2 villagers to wood.

164.title: 6 Forward
164.description: Now send 6 from sheep/boar to the enemy's base to start building towers.

165.title: 3 on Stone
165.description: Send the next 3 villagers to mine stone.

166.title: 2 Sheep → 2 Berries
166.description: Send 2 villagers from sheep to forage berries.

167.title: Loom + 20 Pop Feudal
167.description: Now research loom, and then click Feudal with 20 population.

168.title: 10 Forward
168.description: Now send 10 from sheep/boar to the enemy's base to build a town center right next to theirs.

169.title: Delete and rebuild TC
169.description: Delete your starting TC and rebuild it next to your opponent's TC. Garrison all forward villagers to shoot down the other TC.

170.title: Continue villager prduction
170.description: Continue to produce new villagers in your new TC.

172.description: Now move 4 villagers from sheeps to gold.

173.description: Now move 3 villagers from sheep to gold.

175.title: 2 Sheep → 2 Farms
175.description: Also move 2 villagers from sheep to build farms.

176.title: 2 Sheep → 2 Berries
176.description: Move 2 villagers from sheep to berries.

178.title: 2 Houses + Mill + 4 on Deer
178.description: The next 4 villagers should build a mill next to the deer and hunt. Build 2 houses with the next villager.

179.title: 3 Militia
179.description: Make 3 militia before you reach the Feudal age.

180.title: Forging
180.description: Now research Forging at the blacksmith.

181.title: New Villagers to Food
181.description: Continue producing villagers and send them to food.

182.title: House + Mill + 1 on Berries
182.description: Build a houses and a mill with the next villager and have them collect berries.

183.title: Push Deer (or Go to Berries)
183.description: Push deer or send the next villagers to berries.

184.title: 3 Sheep → 3 Berries
184.description: Now move 3 villagers from sheep to berries as sheep run out.

185.title: 3 Sheep → 3 Farms
185.description: Move 3 villagers to make farms around the TC.

186.title: 2 Sheep → 2 Farms
186.description: Also move 2 villagers from sheep to build farms.

187.title: 3 Berries → 3 Gold
187.description: Now move 3 villagers from berries to gold.

188.title: Barracks
188.description: Now build a barracks before you reach the Castle age.

192.title: Upgrade to Eagle Warriors
192.description: Research Eagle Warriors at the barracks.

193.title: 9 on Gold
193.description: Send the next 9 villagers to gold.

194.title: Produce Monks and Collect Relics
194.description: Send the next 9 villagers to gold.

196.title: Siege Workshop
196.description: Now build a forward siege workshop.

197.title: Build Rams for the Push
197.description: Now start building rams and start pushing.

198.title: Redemption
198.description: Research Redemption at the monestry to convert counter siege such as manganels.

199.title: 10 on Wood
199.description: Send the next 10 villagers to wood.

200.title: 1 House + 5 on Sheep
200.description: Build 1 house, then send our first 5 villagers to sheep.

201.title: 1 House + 2 on Wood
201.description: Build 1 house, then send the next 2 villagers to wood.

202.title: Lure Boar + 3 More on Boar
202.description: Now send the next villager to lure the boar, then add 3 more villager to sheep.

203.title: House + Mill + 2 on Berries
203.description: Build a houses and a mill with the next 2 villagers and have them collect berries.

205.title: 3 Sheep → 3 Wood (Straggler Trees)
205.description: Now move 3 villagers to straggler trees.

206.title: 2 Build a House + 1 Builds a Barracks
206.description: Build 1 house with 2 villagers and build a barracks with your third villager.

207.title: 2 on Wood (Straggler Trees)
207.description: Send 2 villagers to straggler trees near the TC.

208.title: Force Drop Off Wood to Build 2nd House
208.description: Build a house as soon as you can afford it.

209.title: 6 on Sheep (incl. Barracks Builder)
209.description: Send the next 6 villagers to sheep.

211.title: Push 2 Deer
211.description: Push deer to go up faster and save the sheep for later.

212.title: Loom + 21 Pop Feudal
212.description: Now research loom, and then click Feudal with 21 population.

213.title: 2nd Lumber Camp + 2 on Wood
213.description: Build a 2nd lumber camp and spread out your lumber jacks.

214.title: 1 Builds 1 House + Barracks + Houses + Walling
214.description: Build a house and barracks at the front of your base with the next villager.

215.title: Lure Boar
215.description: Now send the next villager to lure the boar.

216.title: Collect 10 Gold
216.description: Collect 10 gold with the next villager without building a mining camp.

217.title: Mill + 5 Sheep → 5 Berries
217.description: When the 2nd boar is almost finished send 5 villagers to make a mill.

218.title: 6 Sheep → 6 Farms
218.description: Build 6 farms with villagers from sheep.

219.title: 4 Sheep → 4 Farms
219.description: Move 4 villagers from sheep to farms.

220.title: 1 Sheep → Straggler Trees
220.description: Move 1 villager from sheep to straggler trees.

221.title: 2 Wood → 2 Gold
221.description: Send 2 lumber jacks to mine gold.

223.title: Double-Bit Axe + Horse Collar
223.description: Research both double- bit axe and horse collar.

224.title: 5 Berries → 5 Wood
224.description: When the berries run out send the foragers to chop wood.

225.title: House + 1 on Stragglers
225.description: Build a house with the next villager and then send them to a straggler tree.

226.title: 2 on Stragglers
226.description: Send the next 3 villager to stragglers tree.

227.title: Lumber Camp + 3 on Wood
227.description: Build a lumber camp and send the next 3 villagers to chop wood.

228.title: 6 on Stone
228.description: Send the next 6 villagers to mine stone.

230.title: Build 2 Castles
230.description: Build 2 castles using all of the villagers from stone.

231.title: 5 Builders → 5 Gold
231.description: Send 5 builders to mine gold once they are done with building.

232.title: 5 Builders → 5 Wood
232.description: Send 5 builders to chop wood once they are done with building.

233.title: 3 on Farms
233.description: Now send the next 3 villagers to build farms.

235.title: Start producing Galleys from 3 docks
235.description: Start building galleys upon reaching Feudal age.

236.title: 5 Fishing Ships
236.description: Make a new fishing ship as soon as you get 75 wood unitl you have 5 fishing ships.

237.title: 4 Berries → 4 Farms
237.description: Now move 4 villagers from berries to farms.

238.title: 2 Sheep → 2 Stone
238.description: Now move another 2 villagers to stone.

239.title: 1 on Wood (Straggler Trees)
239.description: Now send the next villager to straggler trees around the Town Center.

240.title: 4 (5) on Sheep
240.description: Now send the next 4 (or 5) villagers to sheep/boar.

241.title: 10 Sheep → 10 Farms
241.description: Move villagers to farms until you have 10 farms.

242.title: ↑10 Farms
242.description: Move villagers to farms until you have 10 farms.

243.title: 8 on Wood
243.description: Now send the next 8 villagers to wood.

244.title: ↑18 Farms
244.description: Once you have enough villagers on gold, the next villagers should all go to farms. (Set the TC gather point to nearby straggler trees.)

246.title: 3 Sheep → Walling
246.description: Send around 3 from sheep to start walling your base quickly.

248.title: Move to Farms
248.description: Start moving villagers from under the town center to make new farms, every time you have 60 wood in the bank.

249.title: Loom + 16 Pop Feudal
249.description: Now research loom, and then click Feudal with 16 population.

252.title: ↑18 on Farms
252.description: The next 8 villagers should build farms.

253.title: House + Mill + 6 on Berries
253.description: Build a houses and a mill with the next 6 villagers and have them collect berries.

254.title: 1 Lures 2nd Boar + 1 More on Boar
254.description: Send the next villager to lure the 2nd boar and send 1 more to boar.

255.title: Stable + Double-Bit Axe
255.description: Now build a stable with at least 2 villagers, and research double-bit axe.

256.title: Lure Boar With Villager Under TC + 1 on Boar
256.description: Now use one of our villagers underneath the town center to lure the 1st boar.

257.title: 1 Lures 2nd Boar + 2 More on Boar
257.description: Send the next villager to lure the 2nd boar and send 2 more to boar.

258.description: Send the next villager to lure the 2nd boar and send 2 more to boar.

259.title: Loom + 29 Pop Feudal
259.description: Now research loom, and then click Feudal with 29 population.

260.title: Hunt Deer as Sheep Deplete
260.description: Start hunting deer as your sheep deplete.

261.title: Blacksmith + Stable
261.description: Now build a stable and a blacksmith.

262.title: 6 Berries → 6 Wood
262.description: Send all foragers to chop wood.

265.title: 1 Wood + Builder Forward
265.description: Now send the builder + 1 lumber jack forward to build forward buildings.

268.title: Loom + 15 Pop Feudal
268.description: Now research loom, and then click Feudal with 15 population.

269.title: 1 Builds Lumber Camp + Mining Camp
269.description: The next villager builds a mining camp next to gold and a lumber camp.

270.title: 1 Builder + 2 Sheep → 3 Gold
270.description: Send the builder + 1 shepherd to mine gold.

271.title: 11 Sheep → 11 Wood
271.description: Send all villagers below the TC to chop wood.

272.title: 9 Wood → 9 Sheep
272.description: Send 9 villagers from wood to sheep under the TC.

273.title: Move to farms and add villagers slowly
273.description: Move to farms whenever you have 60 wood. Use straggler trees when sheep deplete.

275.title: House + Lumber Camp
275.description: Make a lumber camp and a house as soon as you can afford it.

276.title: 1 Builds Dock
276.description: The next villager builds a dock. If you need to wait for the wood or after the villager is done, let them collect shore fish near the dock.

277.title: 7 Fishing Ships
277.description: Make a new fishing ship as soon as you get 75 wood unitl you have 7 fishing ships.

278.title: Dock Second Pond + 5 Ships
278.description: On Four Lakes, dock a second safe pond. And start producing fishing ships.

279.title: 5 More Fishing Ships
279.description: Make a new fishing ship as soon as you get 75 wood unitl you have 12 fishing ships.

280.title: Bow Saw + Gillnets
280.description: Research both bow saw and gillnets.

281.title: Builder → Shore Fish
281.description: Collect shore fish with the builder near the dock.

282.title: Loom + 18 Pop Feudal
282.description: Now research loom, and then click Feudal with 18 population.

283.title: 1 Sheep → 1 Berries
283.description: Also move 1 villager from the sheep/boar to forage berries.

284.title: 3 Sheep → Forward
284.description: Send 3 villagers forward to build barrack forward.

285.title: Range + Double-Bit Axe
285.description: Now build a range, and research double-bit axe.

287.title: Tower Enemy's Resources
287.description: Build a tower with your forward villagers.

288.title: 3 Builders → 3 Stone
288.description: Move the forward villagers to mine stone.

289.title: 5 Sheep → 5 Farms
289.description: Move 5 villagers from sheep to farms.

290.title: 3 on Wood (Straggler Trees)
290.description: Now send the next 3 villagers to straggler trees around the TC.

291.title: 5 Sheep → 5 Wood (Straggler Trees)
291.description: As sheep deplete, send 5 shepherds to straggler trees around the TC.

292.title: Horse Collar + ↑15 Farms
292.description: Research horse collar before moving the villagers on straggler trees to build new farms.

293.title: 4 Berries → 4 Gold
293.description: Now move 4 villagers from berries to gold.

298.title: 5 on Farms
298.description: The next 5 villagers should build farms.

299.title: Pikeman Upgrade + Infantry Armor
299.description: The next 5 villagers should build farms.

300.title: 1 on Sheep
300.description: Now send the next villager to sheep/boar.

301.title: 1 on Stone
301.description: Send the next villager to mine stone.

302.title: 1 Gold → 1 Stone
302.description: The gold villager should now go to mine stone.

303.title: 4 Sheep → Forward
303.description: Send 4 villagers forward to build barrack forward.

305.title: 5 Sheep → 5 Berries
305.description: When the 2nd boar is almost finished send 5 villagers to berries.

306.title: Idle TC in Feudal Age
306.description: Don't build 2 additional villagers in Feudal Age as you would for a standard Fast Castle build.

307.title: Idle TC in Castle Age
307.description: Don't build additional villagers in Castle Age.

308.title: Husbandry + Scale Barding Armor
308.description: Research Husbandry + Scale Barding Armor when moving to attack.

310.title: House + Lumber Camp
310.description: Send the next villager to build a house and then a lumber camp.

311.title: 2 Build Barracks
311.description: Now build a barracks with the 2 next villagers.

312.title: 2 Builders → 2 Gold
312.description: Send the 2 builders to mine gold.
